comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-03T04:27:39.327Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation evidence: CPU-profiled pm next on this repo (857 items, ~1450 toon files). Dominant costs: (1) each runList re-read+re-parsed metadata-cache.json (3.2MB) and metadata-cache-collections.json (4.9MB) — pm next/context call runList twice, so ~16MB JSON per invocation; (2) Date.parse per comparison in compareTimestampStrings and regex pipeline in normalizeStatusToken inside O(n log n) sort comparators. Fixes: stat-validated in-process memo for the three cache envelopes in front-matter-cache.ts (invalidated on persist + by stat signature; also removes per-call re-parse in the long-lived MCP server), plus capped memos for Date.parse and status-token normalization. Warm timings before→after: next 1282-1545→564-699ms, context 1233-1579→494-703ms, list --status open 987-1042→425-478ms, get 704-762→262-304ms. Behavior verified byte-identical vs published 2026.7.2 on this tracker (next/list/get identical; context differs only in embedded now timestamps). Remaining above-300ms cost for next/context is ~300ms ESM module load + double corpus stat-scan — candidates for a follow-up build-level lazy-load pass."
